name: Bruce Lee
description:
Bruce Lee (Chinese: ; pinyin: Lǐ Zhènfán; 27 November 1940 – 20 July 1973) was a Hong Kong martial arts actor. Bruce Lee was born in San Francisco, but from childhood to adolescence living in Hong Kong, his youth went to college & career in the United States.

As an actor and martial arts expert, Bruce Lee popularized kung fu films throughout the world. He died young in 1973. Bruce Lee studied kung fu siu hong sung, taekwondo (trained with colleagues such as bob wall and chuck norris), wingchun, taichi, fencing, and boxing as well as nunchaku from dan inosanto
